---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<title>OpenClaw Simple - Setup Guides for Complete Beginners</title>
		<meta name="description" content="Honest, simple guides for setting up OpenClaw when you're not technical. No jargon, no assumptions - just step-by-step help that actually works." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="min-h-screen">
			<!-- Header -->
			<header class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
				<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-4">
					<div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
						<span class="text-3xl">ü¶û</span>
						<div>
							<h1 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900">OpenClaw Simple</h1>
							<p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Setup guides for normal humans</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</header>

			<!-- Hero -->
			<section class="py-12 sm:py-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-blue-50 to-white">
				<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
					<h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
						"I heard about OpenClaw.<br />How do I actually set this thing up?"
					</h2>
					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						You're not technical. You've never touched a terminal. You just want an AI assistant that actually <em>does stuff</em> ‚Äî clears your emails, books things, sorts your calendar.
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						The problem? Every guide assumes you know what "SSH" means or how to "deploy to a VPS." 
					</p>
					<p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
						<strong>This site exists because I got frustrated too.</strong> These are the guides I wish existed when I started ‚Äî written for people who don't live in terminals.
					</p>
					<a href="#guides" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-blue-700 transition">
						Show me the guides ‚Üí
					</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- What is OpenClaw (Simple) -->
			<section class="py-12 bg-white">
				<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">What even is OpenClaw?</h3>
					<div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						<p>
							Think of it like having a really capable assistant who lives in your phone or computer. You text it like you'd text a person:
						</p>
						<div class="bg-gray-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 italic">
							<p>"Check my emails and flag anything urgent."</p>
							<p class="mt-2">"Book me a table at that Italian place for Friday at 7."</p>
							<p class="mt-2">"Remind me to call Dave tomorrow morning."</p>
						</div>
						<p>
							And it actually <strong>does it</strong> ‚Äî not just tells you how, but goes and does the thing. Clears your inbox, sends the booking request, sets the reminder.
						</p>
						<p>
							The catch? You have to set it up yourself. And that's where it gets intimidating if you're not a developer.
						</p>
						<p class="font-semibold">
							That's what these guides are for. We'll get you from "I've no idea what I'm doing" to "holy shit, this thing actually works."
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Guides Section -->
			<section id="guides" class="py-12 bg-gray-50">
				<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">The Guides</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-8">Start from the top. Each one builds on the last.</p>
					
					<div class="space-y-4">
						<!-- Guide 1 -->
						<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:shadow-md transition">
							<div class="flex items-start">
								<span class="text-3xl mr-4">1Ô∏è‚É£</span>
								<div class="flex-1">
									<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Installing OpenClaw (15 minutes)</h4>
									<p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Getting OpenClaw running on your computer. Step by step, with screenshots for every single click.</p>
									<span class="inline-block bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 text-sm font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded">Writing now</span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Guide 2 -->
						<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:shadow-md transition opacity-60">
							<div class="flex items-start">
								<span class="text-3xl mr-4">2Ô∏è‚É£</span>
								<div class="flex-1">
									<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Connecting WhatsApp</h4>
									<p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Control it from your phone. No app needed ‚Äî just WhatsApp.</p>
									<span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Coming next</span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Guide 3 -->
						<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:shadow-md transition opacity-60">
							<div class="flex items-start">
								<span class="text-3xl mr-4">3Ô∏è‚É£</span>
								<div class="flex-1">
									<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Teaching It Who You Are</h4>
									<p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Give it context so it actually understands what you need help with.</p>
									<span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Coming soon</span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Guide 4 -->
						<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:shadow-md transition opacity-60">
							<div class="flex items-start">
								<span class="text-3xl mr-4">4Ô∏è‚É£</span>
								<div class="flex-1">
									<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Running It 24/7 (Without Leaving Your Laptop On)</h4>
									<p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Use a cheap server so OpenClaw is always available. Costs about ¬£4/month.</p>
									<span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Coming soon</span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>

						<!-- Guide 5 -->
						<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-5 hover:shadow-md transition opacity-60">
							<div class="flex items-start">
								<span class="text-3xl mr-4">5Ô∏è‚É£</span>
								<div class="flex-1">
									<h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">When Things Break</h4>
									<p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">Common problems and how to fix them without panicking.</p>
									<span class="text-gray-500 text-sm">Coming soon</span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Who Made This -->
			<section class="py-12 bg-white border-t border-gray-200">
				<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Who made this?</h3>
					<div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						<p>
							I'm not a developer. I'm a product person who got excited about OpenClaw, tried to set it up, and spent three frustrating days piecing together Reddit posts and Discord messages.
						</p>
						<p>
							Every guide assumed I knew what a "Docker container" was or how to "SSH into a server." I didn't. I had to learn the hard way.
						</p>
						<p>
							So I'm writing the guides I wish existed ‚Äî for people like me who just want the damn thing to work.
						</p>
						<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 italic">
							(This site isn't affiliated with the OpenClaw project. It's just me, trying to help.)
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Footer -->
			<footer class="bg-gray-50 border-t border-gray-200 py-8">
				<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 text-center text-sm text-gray-600">
					<p class="mb-2">OpenClaw Simple ¬∑ Beginner-friendly guides</p>
					<p>
						<a href="https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">OpenClaw on GitHub</a>
					</p>
				</div>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
